cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.LG. 

The paper deals with game theory applied to wireless networks, specifically spectrum sharing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science - Game Theory and Decision Science). The paper also discusses privacy and truthfulness guarantees, which suggests categories such as cs.CR (Computer Science - Cryptography and Security) and cs.LG (Computer Science - Machine Learning). The use of online learning algorithms and past experience on channel access suggests categories such as cs.NI (Computer Science - Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Computer Science - Information Theory).
